git rm -r cache/ # remove a given folder from a Git repo
git init
git add .
git add file
git status
git clone
git commit # This commits your files to your LOCAL repo, 
             not the one on the server.
git push # This "pushes" your committed changes up to the server.

Tutorial: http://b.lesseverything.com/2008/3/25/got-git-howto-git-and-github

Troubleshooting: http://help.github.com/linux-key-setup/
		 http://help.github.com/troubleshooting-ssh/
------------------------------------------------------------------

Global setup:
 Download and install Git
  git config --global user.name "Your Name"
  git config --global user.email camilobern@gmail.com
        
Next steps:
  mkdir CSC209
  cd CSC209
  git init
  touch README
  git add README
  git commit -m 'first commit'
  git remote add origin git@github.com:camilobern/CSC209.git
  git push origin master
      
Existing Git Repo?
  cd existing_git_repo
  git remote add origin git@github.com:camilobern/CSC209.git
  git push origin master
